name: Judith Rakers
description:
A request of @lemke.

Judith Rakers is a German journalist and TV anchorwoman, mainly known as the host of the news programme Tagesschau on ARD.

1500-step TI trained on a dataset of 18 images with my usual settings.

Appreciate my work? My TIs are free, but you can always buy me a coffee. :)

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

How to create a good prompt using my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. For instance, "photo of (judrak:0.99), a woman, RAW, close portrait photo, black leather jacket, tank top with logo, pale skin, slim body, (high detailed skin:1.2), 8k uhd, dslr, soft lighting, high quality, film grain, Fujifilm XT3 sharp focus, f 5.6, long blonde hair".
